    addNode(108, "RefPedia_presentation.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "RefPedia — App Overview\n\nRefPedia is a mobile app for aspiring and active basketball referees to learn, practice, and test their officiating skills. Available on iOS and Android, it combines video lessons, interactive quizzes, camera-based exercises, and exam simulations — all in one app.\n\n\"Turn your passion for basketball into professional skills!\" 🏀\n\nThe Challenge\n\nTraditional referee training relies on rulebooks and in-person clinics: slow, inflexible, and non-interactive. There was no mobile tool to study, practice, and test referees on the go.\n\nOur Solution\n\nRefPedia integrates five learning modules:\n\nModule	What It Does\n📹 Video Lessons	Curated tutorials on rules, fouls, and signals.\n🎬 Video Quiz	Identify calls from real game footage; typo-tolerant answers.\n✋ Hand Signal Recognition	Image-based quiz with automatic retry for wrong answers.\n📷 Camera Practice	Perform hand signals via camera, review, redo, and confirm.\n📝 Theoretical Exam	True/False practice or timed exam (30 min, 80% pass).\nKey Features\nAuthentication: Email/password or Google Sign-In, with Guest mode.\nUser Profile: Update credentials and submit feedback.\nNotifications: In-app system synced via Firebase.\nAdmin Panel: Add/edit questions, manage feedback, moderate content.\nAI Moderation: Gemini 1.5 Flash filters toxic/off-topic feedback automatically.\nUser Flow\nWelcome\n ├─ Sign Up → Home\n ├─ Login → Home\n └─ Guest → Home\n\nHome\n ├─ Learn (Video Lessons)\n ├─ Recognise Hand Signals\n ├─ Practice Hand Signals (Camera)\n ├─ Video Test\n ├─ Theoretical Exam\n ├─ Notifications\n └─ Profile (Update, Feedback, Logout)\nAudience & Platforms\nUsers: Basketball referees, instructors, and enthusiasts.\nPlatforms: iOS ✅ | Android ✅ ", 7);
    addNode(109, "RefPedia_documantation", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "RefPedia — Technical Overview\nTech Stack\nFrontend: React Native (Expo), JavaScript (ES2020+)\nRouting: Expo Router (file-based navigation)\nBackend: Firebase (Authentication, Firestore, Storage)\nAI Moderation: Google Gemini API\nMedia: expo-video / expo-av (video), expo-camera\nStorage: AsyncStorage (local), Firestore (cloud)\nArchitecture\n\nRefPedia follows a modular, component-based architecture with clear separation between UI, logic, and services.\n\nApp Layer: File-based routing with dedicated screens (auth, learning, quizzes, profile, feedback)\nComponents: Reusable UI elements (buttons, inputs, layouts)\nServices: Firebase integration and user data handling\nState Management: React Context (AuthProvider)\nCore Features\nAuthentication: Email/password + Google Sign-In (OAuth)\nLearning System: Video lessons and interactive quizzes\nPractice Mode: Camera-based hand signal training\nExams: Timed and practice theoretical tests\nFeedback System: Admin/user roles with AI moderation\nNotifications: In-app messaging system\nDatabase Design (Firestore)\n\nKey collections:\n\nusers → roles (admin/user)\nenunturi → quiz questions (true/false)\ncamera → practice tasks\nfeedback → user feedback + replies\nmessages → notifications\nSecurity\nFirebase Authentication for user management\nRole-based access control (admin vs user)\nAI-powered content moderation (Gemini API)\nSecure data handling via Firebase rules\nDesign System\nResponsive UI: Custom hp/wp scaling functions\nConsistent Styling: Centralized theme (colors, typography, spacing)\nMobile-first UX: Optimized for clarity and usability", 7);
    addNode(110, "RefPedia_terms&conditions.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "By using RefPedia, you agree to these terms.\nEffective / Last Updated: March 21, 2026\n\n1. Use of the App\nRefPedia is an educational tool for learning basketball refereeing. It is intended for personal, non-commercial use only. You agree to use the app responsibly and in accordance with applicable laws.\n\n2. Accounts & Access\nSome features require an account. You are responsible for keeping your login details secure. Guest mode offers limited access without registration.\n\n3. Content & Intellectual Property\nAll app content (videos, quizzes, design, etc.) is protected and may not be copied or reused without permission. Basketball rules themselves remain public domain.\n\n4. User Conduct\nYou agree not to misuse the app, attempt unauthorized access, or submit harmful, offensive, or irrelevant content.\n\n5. Data & Privacy\nWe collect minimal data (email, app usage, feedback). We do not collect sensitive data such as photos (stored locally only) or location data. Services like Firebase and Google Sign-In may process data according to their policies.\n\n6. Feedback & Moderation\nUser feedback may be moderated automatically. Inappropriate content may be removed.\n\n7. Disclaimer\nThe app is provided “as is” without guarantees of accuracy or availability. RefPedia does not provide official certification.\n\n8. Liability\nWe are not responsible for any damages resulting from the use of the app.\n\n9. Changes\nTerms may be updated at any time. Continued use means you accept the changes.\n\n10. Contact\nmihai.arisanu2006@gmail.com", 7);
