    addNode(114, "NightDrive_presentation.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — App Overview\n\nNightDrive is a real-time, community-driven navigation app for car enthusiasts who value the experience of driving as much as the destination. Featuring a sleek OLED-friendly dark UI and social hazard reporting, it redefines night driving.\n\n\"Navigate the night. Own the road.\"\n\nThe Challenge\n\nTraditional GPS apps focus only on routes and shortest paths, lacking interactivity, social connection, and night-optimized design.\n\nOur Solution\n\nNightDrive integrates navigation, community, and social features:\n\nFeature	What It Does\nNight-Mode Navigation:\n	OLED-friendly dark maps with live GPS, speed, and heading. Cinematic camera tilt above 5 km/h.\nSmart Routing:\n	Turn-by-turn directions with dead-reckoning for GPS loss and auto-rerouting.\nReal-Time Event Reporting:\n	Community-reported hazards (accidents, police, potholes) with upvote validation.\nDriver Network:\n	Unique hex tags, friend requests, and in-app messaging.\nSecure Authentication:\n	JWT sessions, Bcrypt password hashing, persistent login.\nSaved Places & Preferences:\n	Bookmark destinations, avoid disliked streets, save favorite routes.\nProfile Management:\n	Edit profile, change avatar/email, delete account GDPR-compliantly.\n\nDesign Philosophy\nOLED-First: Pure black backgrounds for eye comfort and battery savings.\nNeon Accents: Purple highlights for a cyberpunk feel.\nMinimalist HUD: Essential info within thumb reach.\nGlassmorphism: Floating translucent bars for modern aesthetic.\nZero UI Clutter: Focus on the road, hide unnecessary overlays.\nUser Flow:\nWelcome → Login/Register → Main Map\n           					↘ Menu → Profile / Friends / Saved Places / Events\nArchitecture\nClient: React Native (TypeScript)\nBackend: Go (REST API)\nDatabase: PostgreSQL + PostGIS\nReal-Time: WebSocket support for live updates\nAuth: JWT + Bcrypt\nDeployment: Docker Compose (Client + API + DB)\nWhy NightDrive Stands Out\nAspect	Traditional GPS	NightDrive\nDesign	Bright, generic UI	OLED-dark, cyberpunk style\nCommunity	Passive	Active social cruising\nHazards	Limited	Night-focused, verified\nGPS Loss	Freezes	Dead-reckoning simulation\nIdentity	Email/Name	Unique hex tag\nRoad Preferences	None	Avoid disliked streets\nTarget Users\nNight drivers & urban commuters\nCar enthusiasts & social cruisers\nDrivers who want real-time hazard alerts\nRoadmap\nLive friend tracking\nGroup cruises & coordinated drives\nLeaderboards for verified reporting\nVoice alerts for hands-free safety\nAI-based road quality scoring\n\nNightDrive — Navigate the night. Own the road. 🌙", 8);
    addNode(115, "NightDrive_documentation", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — Technical Overview\n\nNightDrive is a real-time, community-driven night navigation app. Built with React Native, Go, and PostgreSQL/PostGIS, it emphasizes immersive night driving, social connectivity, and hazard reporting.\n\nArchitecture\n\nMonorepo structure with three core services orchestrated via Docker Compose:\n\nClient (React Native)  ↔  Backend API (Go)  ↔  PostgreSQL + PostGIS\n     Port:8081             Port:8080            Port:5432\nCommunication: RESTful JSON + WebSocket (real-time events)\nDeployment: Docker Compose (frontend + backend + DB)\nTechnology Stack\nLayer	Technology\nClient	React Native (TypeScript), React Navigation, Google Maps SDK, AsyncStorage, Hooks for GPS & dead reckoning\nBackend	Go (Golang), net/http, JWT auth, Bcrypt password hashing\nDatabase	PostgreSQL 15 + PostGIS 3.4 (spatial queries)\nContainerization	Docker Compose\nProject Structure (Simplified)\nnightdrive-main/\n├── client/      # React Native app\n├── api/         # Go backend\n├── docker-compose.yml\n\nClient Highlights:\n\nMainScreen.tsx — Map, real-time location, dead reckoning, event reporting\nMenuScreen.tsx — Profile, friends, saved places, disliked streets\nCustom hooks: useLocation, useDeadReckoning, useRerouting\n\nBackend Highlights:\n\nEndpoints: /users, /login, /me, /events, /friends, /ws\nHandlers: User management, event creation, vote handling, WebSocket updates\nModels: User, Event\nCore Features\nNavigation & Spatial\nGPS tracking with speed & heading\nDead reckoning simulation during GPS loss\nAuto-rerouting if deviation > 50m\nSpatial queries via PostGIS (ST_DWithin)\nEvent Reporting\nTypes: Accident, Police, Hazard, Roadworks\nCommunity upvote/downvote validation\nAutomatic expiration after timestamp\nSocial System\nUnique 4-character hex tags (#4Z9C) for identity\nFriend requests: search by tag, accept/reject, store friendships\nAuthentication\nJWT tokens (72-hour expiry)\nPassword hashing with Bcrypt\nPersistent storage in AsyncStorage\nDatabase Schema (Highlights)\nTable	Purpose\nusers	User profiles with tags, points, trust score\nevents	Geo-located reports with upvotes/downvotes\nfriend_requests	Pending friend requests\nfriendships	Established friendships (ordered to prevent duplicates)\nsaved_routes	User-saved routes with start/end points\nDeployment & Env Variables\n\nDocker Compose services:\n\ndb: PostgreSQL + PostGIS\nnightdrive-backend: Go API\nnightdrive-frontend: React Native\n\nQuick start:\n\ndocker-compose up --build\n\nKey environment variables:\n\nAPI_BASE_URL, GOOGLE_API_GENERAL_KEY (client)\nDB_USER, DB_PASSWORD, DB_NAME, DB_HOST, DB_PORT (backend)", 8);
    addNode(116, "NightDrive_terms&conditions.txt", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "NightDrive — Terms & Conditions\n\nEffective / Last Updated: March 21, 2026\n\nNightDrive is a community-driven navigation app for car enthusiasts, providing real-time GPS navigation, social features, and crowd-sourced road event reporting. By using the App, users agree to comply with these Terms.\n\n1. User Eligibility & Accounts\nMust be ≥18 years old or legal driving age.\nValid driver’s license required if using while driving.\nAccount creation requires email, username, password, and generates a unique driver tag (e.g., #4Z9C).\nUsers are responsible for account security. Account deletion permanently removes data and friend connections.\n2. Acceptable Use\n\nUsers must:\n\nFollow traffic laws and report accurate road events.\nTreat other users respectfully.\n\nProhibited activities:\n\nUnsafe interaction while driving.\nFalse reports or vote manipulation.\nUnauthorized access, impersonation, or automated scraping.\n3. Driving Safety Disclaimer\nNightDrive is informational only; the driver is always responsible.\nGPS, dead reckoning, and community reports may contain errors.\nDo not use App features as a substitute for vehicle instruments.\nNightDrive and affiliates are not liable for accidents, fines, or damages.\n4. Community Content\nUsers are responsible for accuracy and legality of reports.\nEvent upvote/downvote system helps validate content but is not guaranteed.\nNightDrive may remove content violating Terms.\n5. Intellectual Property & Licensing\nApp code, design, logos, and brand are owned by NightDrive.\nLimited, personal-use license granted to users.\nThird-party services (Google Maps, PostGIS) are subject to their own terms.\n6. Privacy & Data\n\nCollected Data:\n\nAccount (email, username, tag, password hash)\nLocation (GPS) during active navigation\nUsage data (events, votes, friends, saved places)\nDevice info\n\nUsage: To provide navigation, social, and event features.\n\nSecurity:\n\nPasswords hashed via bcrypt\nAPI calls secured with JWT tokens\nEncrypted transmission\n\nSharing: Only with law enforcement, legal process, or essential service providers.\n\nUser Rights: Access, correct, delete, export data; withdraw consent at any time.\n\n7. Liability & Indemnification\nApp is provided “as is”; no warranties.\nNightDrive not liable for indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.\nUsers indemnify NightDrive for claims arising from misuse or illegal activity.\n8. Termination\nUsers can delete accounts anytime.\nNightDrive may suspend accounts for violations or malicious activity.\nLiability, IP, and indemnification clauses survive termination.\n9. Modifications & Governing Law\nTerms may be updated; continued use = acceptance.\nGoverned by Romanian law, jurisdiction of Bucharest courts.\n10. Contact\nEmail: mihai.arisanu2006@gmail.com", 8);
