    addNode(121, "Portofolio_descriere", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "A web portfolio is more than just a digital resume; it's an opportunity to express your mindset and personality through code. Instead of relying on bloated modern frameworks, I chose to build this portfolio from scratch—engineering a custom terminal operating system powered by a C++ kernel and WebAssembly. No excess, no distractions.", 9);
    addNode(122, "Portofolio_documentation", "txt", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "MihaiArisanuOS\n\nA custom, interactive terminal-based portfolio simulating a lightweight Operating System directly in the browser. Built with a unique architecture that bridges a modern Headless CMS with a custom C++ kernel compiled to WebAssembly (WASM).\n\nArchitecture\nUnlike traditional React portfolios, MaOS separates the core logic from the UI:\n\nFrontend (UI): React + Vite. Handles terminal rendering, keyboard inputs, and visual animations.\n\nKernel & Virtual File System (VFS): C++. Manages the file hierarchy, navigation logic, and state. Compiled to WebAssembly for near-native performance.\n\nBackend / CMS: Sanity.io. Acts as the single source of truth for all content (files, directories, links, bio).\n\n🚀 How It Works (The Data Pipeline)\nTo maintain maximum performance without querying a database on every render, the project uses a custom build pipeline:\n\nContent is written and managed in Sanity CMS.\n\nA custom Node.js script (generateVFS.mjs) fetches the structured data via Sanity's API.\n\nThe script automatically writes the C++ code (vfs.cpp), injecting the content directly into the memory structure of the C++ Kernel.\n\nThe C++ code is compiled via Emscripten into core.wasm and core.js.\n\nReact mounts the WASM module and interacts with the engine instantly.\n\nTech Stack\nUI: React, Vite, CSS (Custom Terminal Aesthetics)\n\nCore Logic: C++, WebAssembly (WASM), Emscripten\n\nContent Management: Sanity.io, Node.js, @sanity/client", 9);
    addNode(123, "Portofolio_github.sh", "exec", "4.0 K", "2026-03-21", "https://github.com/MihaiArisanu/WebPortofolio", 9);
